we get that $\sin{a} = \frac{\sqrt{15} \pm 2\sqrt{2}}{6}, \sin{b} = \frac{\sqrt{15} \mp 2\sqrt{2}}{6}$, so $\cos{(a-b)} = 1 - 2\sin{a}\sin{b} = \boxed{\pm\frac{1}{3}}$. <answer> $\pm\frac{1}{3}$ </answer>

